Several provincial departments raided preschools in Sophiatown. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Early childhood development is in crisis. That’s the word from the City of Johannesburg after it shut down two illegal childcare centres. Several provincial departments raided pre-schools in Sophiatown on Wednesday. READ: Police confirm crèche teacher's arrest for abuse The operation follows the deaths of two children at an unregistered crèche in the area, apparently after they ingested rat poison. More raids are expected.